University of Leipzig, Philipp Rosenthalstr. 23-25, Leipzig D-4103, Germany. 
dietger@medizin.uni-leipzig.de

With increasing donor age, the potential of transmitting diseases from donor to 
recipient reaches new dimensions. Potentially transmittable diseases from donors 
include infections, congenital disorders, and acquired illnesses like autoimmune 
diseases or malignancies of hematological or nonhematological origin. While 
established nonmalignant or malignant diseases might be easy to discover, 
early-stage hematological diseases like CML, light-chain multiple myelomas, 
aleukemic leukemias, occult myelodysplastic syndromes and other malignant and 
